==English==
===Etymology===
This common name presumably comes from the tendency of such creatures, when in their adult phase attached to rocks, to squirt out water at low tide when exposed or only just covered.
===Noun===
'''[[sea]] [[squirt]]'''
# Marine creatures of the species ''[[Urochordata]]'' (also called ''[[Tunicata]]'') which live by filtering [[plankton]] or [[nutrient]]s from [[seawater]].
